  "prompt": "Who is the old man in the MDH Masala ads and why does he appear in all their ads?",
  "response": "The old man in the MDH (Mahashian Di Hatti) masala advertisements is Mahashay Dharmpal Gulati, the founder of MDH Spices. He was popularly known as \"Dadaji\" and was a well-known face in Indian television commercials. \n\nSome key points about him:\n\n1. He founded MDH Spices in 1959 and transformed it from a small spice shop in Sialkot (now in Pakistan) to a major spice brand in India.\n\n2. He became synonymous with the brand through his personal appearances in advertisements, which gave the brand a personal and trustworthy image.\n\n3. His warm, grandfatherly demeanor and sincere way of speaking made him very popular and relatable to Indian consumers.\n\n4. He was known for his simple and direct style of promoting the brand's spices.\n\n5. Mahashay Dharmpal Gulati passed away on December 3, 2022, at the age of 97, leaving behind a significant legacy in the Indian spice industry.\n\nHis appearances in advertisements were a unique marketing strategy that helped build trust and recognition for the MDH brand over several decades.",
